titleStmt.funder: Gos 2.0, Artur: Operacijo "Razvoj slovenščine v digitalnem okolju" sta sofinancirala Republika Slovenija in Evropska unija iz Evropskega sklada za regionalni razvoj. Operacija se je izvajala v okviru Operativnega programa za izvajanje evropske kohezijske politike v obdobju 2014-2020.

Gos 2.0, Artur: The operation "Development of Slovene in a Digital Environment" was co-financed by the Republic of Slovenia and the European Union under the European Regional Development Fund. The project was carried out under the Operational Programme for the Implementation of the EU Cohesion Policy in the period 2014 – 2020.
Gos 1.1: Projekt je sofinancirala raziskovalna infrastruktura CLARIN.SI
Gos 1.1: The project was co-financed by the CLARIN.SI research infrastructure.

Gos 1.0: Operacijo delno financira Evropska unija iz Evropskega socialnega sklada ter Ministrstvo za šolstvo in šport. Operacija se izvaja v okviru Operativnega programa razvoja človeških virov za obdobje 2007/2013, razvojne prioritete: razvoj človeških virov in vseživljenjskega učenja; prednostne usmeritve: izboljšanje kakovosti in učinkovitosti sistemov izobraževanja in usposabljanja 2007/2013.

Gos 1.0: The operation is partly financed by the European Union, the European Social Fund, and the Ministry of Education and Sport of the Republic of Slovenia. The operation is being carried out within the operational programme Human Resources Development for the period 2007/2013, developmental priorities: improvement of the quality and efficiency of educational and training systems 2007/2013.
GosVL: Projekt je financiralo Ministrstvo za kulturo Republike Slovenije (št. projekta 3340-15-141005) in raziskovalna infrastruktura CLARIN.SI
GosVL: The project was financed by the Ministry of Culture of the Republic of Slovenia (grant no. 3340-15-141005) and the CLARIN.SI research infrastructure

sourceDesc.p: Selected parts of the Artur 1.1 corpus, http://hdl.handle.net/11356/1772.

projectDesc.p: Cilj projekta "Razvoj slovenščine v digitalnem okolju" je zadovoljiti potrebe po računalniških izdelkih in storitvah s področja jezikovnih tehnologij za slovenski jezik za raziskovalne organizacije, za podjetja in za širšo javnost.

The goal of the project "Development of Slovene in a Digital Environment" is to facilitate the development of computational tools and services in the field of language technologies for Slovene, which will be used by research organizations, companies, and the general public.

transcriptionDesc.p: Vsi prepisi so bili narejeni ročno in skrbno preverjeni. Prepisi v glavnem sledijo proporočilom za korpus Gos. Za izdelavo prepisov je bilo uporabljeno orodje Transcriber. Uporabi se ga lahko tudi za branje ali izvoz prepisov (datotek .trs) v druge formate.

All transcriptions were done manually and carefully checked. The main guidelines for transcription were those of the Gos corpus. The transcription tool Transcriber was used for making transcriptions. It can be also used for reading or exporting transcriptions (.trs files) to different formats.

application.label: CLASSLA
application.desc: Oblikoskladenjsko označevanje in lematizacija dodana s programom CLASSLA (veja programa Stanza) z modelom za slovenski jezik. CLASSLA is available from https://github.com/clarinsi/classla.
Part-of-speech tagging and lemmatisation performed with CLASSLA (a fork of Stanza) with the model for Slovene, available from https://github.com/clarinsi/classla.

prefixDef.p: Zasebni naslovi URI s to predpono kažejo na knjižnico elementov struktur lastnosti, ki definirajo slovenske oblikoskladenjske oznake MULTEXT-East, različica 6. Datoteka je priložena korpusu, medtem ko je kanonična knjižnica dostopna na https://nl.ijs.si/ME/V6 (datoteka msd/tables/msd-fslib2-sl.xml) in na GitHubu.

Private URIs with this prefix point to the library of feature-structure elements defining the Slovenian MULTEXT-East Version 6 MSDs. The file with this library accompanies the corpus, while the canonical library is available from https://nl.ijs.si/ME/V6 (file msd/tables/msd-fslib2-sl.xml) and on GitHub.
